President Biden addressed the Europa Building in Brussels, Belgium, expressing his commitment to strengthening the partnership between the United States and Europe. He emphasized the shared democratic values and the need to protect them from attacks. Biden highlighted the significant changes happening globally, driven by technology and causing anxiety and uncertainty for many people. He stressed the importance of economic growth, job creation, and preserving the dignity of workers. Biden also mentioned the urgency of addressing climate change and creating well-paying jobs in the green economy. He acknowledged the challenges posed by COVID-19 and the need for transatlantic cooperation to improve living standards for people worldwide. Biden expressed optimism for the future, citing the younger generation's education, openness, and commitment to positive change. He concluded by encouraging further discussion on these topics.